//@version=5
indicator("ta/mfi")
// Test ta.mfi (Money Flow Index)
//
// The first bar's change is na, and an na ternary condition takes the else
// branch, so that bar's flow counts towards BOTH the up and the down sum. That
// is why the first reading is not yet saturated: once the first bar rolls out
// of the window, only same-direction flow is left.

// Bars: 4

// Every fixture bar closes higher than the last.
mfiUp = ta.mfi(close, 3)
log.info(str.tostring(mfiUp))

// Negating the source makes every bar a down bar, mirroring the index.
mfiDown = ta.mfi(-close, 3)
log.info(str.tostring(mfiDown))

// Expected output:
// NaN
// NaN
// NaN
// NaN
// 75.1259802774245
// 24.874019722575497
// 100
// 0
